<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-21T02:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-21T02:44:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.635 Neep/62: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-21T07:00:00-00:44">April 21, 1938—7
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. I have informed President Barclay orally of contents of first 3
                                paragraphs your telegram No. 13, April 12, noon. He is considering
                                    <pb facs="0794" n="786" xml:id="pg_786"/> the suggestion in
                                paragraph 2 and I am awaiting his decision; he states that he much
                                prefers line suggested in paragraph 3.</p>
                            <p>I inquired about preliminary report referred to in paragraph 4 which
                                I am now informed is dated March 6, 1935, and signed by H. Terpstra
                                and V. D. Hoff.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>